The paper introduces a new module for deep convolutional neural networks that improves classification results on benchmark datasets. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on the use of multi-scale convolutional filters, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of maxout activation units, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL), suggesting that this sub-category is also a possibility.
